### TITLE ###
FallbackStripsNullFromLeft
### DESCRIPTION ###
`x ?? 0` where x: int? strips null from the left, result is int.
### INPUT ###
fn f(x: int?):
    y = x ?? 0
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  y @ 2:5 -> <no-type>
  x @ 2:9 -> int?

# Symbol types
  f (fn): fn(int?)
  x (param): int?
  y (local): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
FallbackOnNonNullableLeftKeepsBothArms
### DESCRIPTION ###
When left has no nullable component, fallback can't fire - but we
keep both arms as the conservative answer.
### INPUT ###
y = 5 ?? "fallback"
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  y @ 1:1 -> <no-type>

# Symbol types
  y (local): int|str

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
CatchExprStripsErrorFromLeft
### DESCRIPTION ###
`parse_int(...) catch 0` strips error from the int|error left,
result is int.
### INPUT ###
y = parse_int("5") catch 0
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  y @ 1:1 -> <no-type>
  parse_int @ 1:5 -> dynamic

# Symbol types
  y (local): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
